reviews.title: Perfect summer pant
reviews.body: These pants are lightweight without feeling flimsy or cheap. They wash wonderfully. The navy is a little deeper than the picture but that is not a bad thing.  I am 5' 6.5" and the length is exactly right.  I love the low waist that doesn't leave the crotch of my pants almost at my knees.I didn't think I would like the elastic waist because I have serious tactile sensitivity but the waist is soft and not too tight. The cut is flattering and the pockets are roomy. I DO have to tie my pants a little tighter if my phone rides in the back pocket but it doesn't matter because they are so comfy.I work with kids in the summer and these pants are perfect for all of the physical activities I do at work. But I am really looking forward to taking them on vacation!
reviews.body_html:
These pants are lightweight without feeling flimsy or cheap. They wash wonderfully. The navy is a little deeper than the picture but that is not a bad thing. I am 5' 6.5" and the length is exactly right. I love the low waist that doesn't leave the crotch of my pants almost at my knees.

reviews.title: Lovely but LOW rise - fits petite rise w/curves or reg w/thin hips
reviews.body: I love them. Stone color is beautiful. Perfect linen pant if you are petite rise normally or have thin, straight hips.Great tailoring, lovely seams, but it is made very low rise and form fitting through the hips without stretch. Material is good - “linen thin” (a bit see through - must skin match bikini). This form fits (not loose baggy) but looks  very nice when it fits.This is not for people with a long waist or very curvy unless you really size up. Also, be prepared to hem if you aren’t very tall.If  you do not have a short waist, this will be VERY low. I fit petite and it is a nice low on me. The way they elasticize the top prevents “plumber pants” when you bend, but it fits about at your bikini line -even with a short waist- if you have curves. If you are stick thin and straight all the way down, this fits like on the models. The more curve you have, the lower and tighter it goes.For size, use same size as your form-fitted, tailored zipper pants- maybe even up a size. The elastic waist is purely to accommodate you when you bend. This is not a baggy, loose pull-on (even though it pulls on comfortably .) I imagine even the XXL will not accommodate above a size 12/14.Hope this is helpful!
reviews.body_html:
I love them. Stone color is beautiful. Perfect linen pant if you are petite rise normally or have thin, straight hips.

Great tailoring, lovely seams, but it is made very low rise and form fitting through the hips without stretch. Material is good - “linen thin” (a bit see through - must skin match bikini). This form fits (not loose baggy) but looks very nice when it fits.

This is not for people with a long waist or very curvy unless you really size up. Also, be prepared to hem if you aren’t very tall.

If you do not have a short waist, this will be VERY low. I fit petite and it is a nice low on me. The way they elasticize the top prevents “plumber pants” when you bend, but it fits about at your bikini line -even with a short waist- if you have curves. If you are stick thin and straight all the way down, this fits like on the models. The more curve you have, the lower and tighter it goes.

For size, use same size as your form-fitted, tailored zipper pants- maybe even up a size. The elastic waist is purely to accommodate you when you bend. This is not a baggy, loose pull-on (even though it pulls on comfortably .) I imagine even the XXL will not accommodate above a size 12/14.
Hope this is helpful!

reviews.title: Ultra low-rise
reviews.body: I wanted to like these pants more than I do. The fabric is nice, light and breezy. They've held up to washing. However, the rise is ridiculously low. (And I wear pretty low rise underwear, so we're not talking high waist granny panties or anything here.) You ever find yourself strolling up to a store entrance just to realize that half your thong is peeking out of your pants? No? Well, I have. And have you ever had to duck behind a trash can in a parking lot in broad daylight just to surreptitiously hike your pants at least an inch above your butt crack, tie your drawstring, and do it all without getting arrested for indecent exposure? No? Then don't buy these pants.Mind you, they're OK for lounging around at home, as long as I make sure to give them a good hike and re-tie before I answer the doorbell. But the only way I can make them work in public is to wear them with a long top: I'm neither young nor thin enough to get away with the alternative.

reviews.title: Incorrect size labeling.
reviews.body: I am usually a Large to XL so I bought an XL and it was too tight. The pockets were puckering. I knew that the front was very low-waisted (this is why I bought them; I have bloating from Endometriosis), but they are way too low-waisted in the back, too. There is no way you can wear any kind of underwear without it poking out the back. Also, these are see-through. Other than that, the shape of the leg was nice and they are flattering on the butt.
